It closed on October 9, 2008 after 125 days of release, grossing $215.4 million in the United States and Canada and $416.3 million overseas for a worldwide total of $631.7 million.  Kung Fu Panda was the highest-grossing non-Shrek film from DreamWorks Animation in the USA.

In total grosses, the biggest foreign market for The Croods was China with $63.3 million, becoming the highest grossing original animated film, surpassing DreamWorks Animation's film Kung Fu Panda. The film earned $43.1 million in the United Kingdom, Ireland and Malta.

In North America, The Croods earned $11.6 million on its opening day.  On its opening weekend, the film topped the box office with $43.6 million from 4,046 locations, a vast improvement over the DreamWorks Animation's directly preceding release Rise of the Guardians.

The Croods is the eleventh highest grossing 2013 film, and the fourth highest grossing 2013 animated film (behind Frozen, Despicable Me 2, and Monsters University). It became the second highest grossing original DreamWorks Animation film, behind Kung Fu Panda.
